RAJI ADEBAYO Asiwaju Adekola Adeoye, the former People’s Democratic Party (PDP) youth leader in Oyo State, has described the former governor of the state and the Otun Olubadan of Ibadanland, High Chief Rashidi Adewolu Ladoja, as an exemplary traditional and indefatigable leader. Adeoye stated this in a message on Sunday to Baami Ladoja as he fondly called the former governor, whom he described as his father, noting that Senator Ladoja’s contributions to the progress and development of the state and the country were immeasurable and exemplary. Adeoye said Baami Ladoja is worthy of celebration for the different roles he played in different spheres as an achiever in business, a worthy model in politics and a committed community leader. According to him, “Our father, the Otun Olubadan of Ibadanland, Senator Rashidi Ladoja, I rejoice with you always Baami. “Your life of service, your people-oriented leadership and your immense contributions to the progress and development of Oyo State are exemplary. “I pray to God to grant you good health, long life and more wisdom to make more impact on humanity,” he prayed.